summary: This document details the execution of a search warrant on August 12, 2019, during which FBI agents conducted a three-dimensional laser scan of various locations on Little Saint James Island in the U.S. Virgin Islands. The scans focused on the 'Main Structure Area' and a 'Grotto' on the island, with accompanying data and project files documented for further analysis.

persons.name: Special Agent
persons.context: A Special Agent from the FBI New York Field Office was involved in the execution of the search warrant and the scanning process.

persons.name: Staff Operations Specialist
persons.context: A Staff Operations Specialist from the FBI participated in the evidence response team during the search warrant execution.

events.title: Search Warrant Execution
events.description: FBI agents executed a search warrant and conducted a three-dimensional laser scan of locations on Little Saint James Island.

locations: Little Saint James Island, Virgin Islands, United States
keyFacts: The document describes the execution of a search warrant on August 12, 2019.
FBI agents conducted a three-dimensional laser scan of the 'Main Structure Area' and a 'Grotto' on Little Saint James Island.
The document includes references to various data and project files related to the scans.
